3.3 Community Edition Limitations

a. Kafka Topic Limitation: Each Kafka topic created or used by the Licensed Work is
limited to a maximum of 3 partitions per topic when the Licensed Work is used under
this License. There is no limit on the number of topics or deployments unless otherwise
stated.

b. Enforcement: If the Licensed Work detects any Kafka topic configured with more than
3 partitions while operating under this License, the Licensed Work may refuse to operate
for that topic (for example, refuse to start, disable processing for the topic, or
otherwise block functionality that depends on that topic) until the partition count is
reduced or a commercial license is obtained from Licensor.

